The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                               BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, March 19: The Centre has sanctioned projects worth over Rs 4,500 crore under the Jawaharlal Nehru Urban Renewal Mission. The projects include development and beautification of riverfronts at Sovabazar in Calcutta, Budge Budge and Maheshtala in South 24-Parganas and Rishra and Chandernagore in Hooghly.         
	Calcutta: The Emp- loyees State Insurance (ESI) Corporation will issue smart cards to all workers in the state to ensure hassle-free treatment in its hospitals. The card, with an employees personal details, will have to be produced at ESI hospitals for treatment.                                                                                                                                                                       
